<p><em>TL;DR</em>: The ideal interface is your Mom. She doesnâ€™t need to show you a chart, she just needs to say â€˜Youâ€™re tired, you need to go to bed.â€™ You do it because you trust her and you know sheâ€™s right. Charts are fun and pretty, but only a persuasion stopgap or a presentation aid to help you understand. Digging into data is a fleeting joy. Using a chart to illustrate a correlation can be helpful. Make it Pertinent, Pretty, Polite, and Protected.</p>

